	(text "There's no real chassis or a case to mount the PCB,\nso just place the mounting holes at the corners of the PCB."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 116.078 181.61 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "5571a628-e5ce-4932-aa05-15b27a6c8f99")
	)
	(text "This is a project for practicing PCB design and programming.\n\nThe result is a device that is powered either with a battery or with a USB connection.\nThe device can recharge the battery via the USB connection.\n\nThe device includes:\n  - An example sensor (temperature)\n  - External flash for updating the firmware over the air (FOTA)\n  - A modem module that connects the main microcontroller to the internet with LTE CAT-M1\n  - Option to use either an external antenna or an integrated antenna\n\nA key goal of the project is to ensure it has as little reliance as possible on totalitarian\ncountries (e.g., China or Russia) or on hostile countries (e.g., USA).\nComponent sourcing must be done carefully to select manufacturers who can supply parts that are not\nproduced in such countries.\nInstead, democratic countries (e.g., Taiwan and Germany) should be preferred.\n\nTo reduce strain on the global environment, manufacturing and sourcing is centered around Europe."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
